## Fields

- `occupation` — English free-text role family derived from the title + role context. Examples: `"backend engineering"`, `"registered nursing"`, `"store management"`, `"fleet operations"`, `"tax law"`, `"secondary education"`, `"machine operation"`. **Not** the literal title.
- `seniority` — English free-text seniority / rank. Examples: `"senior"`, `"staff engineer"`, `"junior"`, `"lead"`, `"senior partner"`, `"charge nurse"`, `"department head"`, `"vp"`, `"intern"`. `null` if unclear.
- `employment_type` — one of: `"full_time"`, `"part_time"`, `"contract"`, `"internship"`, `"fellowship"`, `"apprenticeship"`, `"temporary"`, `"volunteer"`, or `null`.
- `locales_in_posting` — ISO-639-1 codes for the language(s) used in the description. Usually one; sometimes two (multilingual EU postings).
- `locations` — array of objects, one per distinct location mentioned:
  ```
  {"raw": "<verbatim as written>", "city": "<English>", "region": "<state/province code or name>",
   "country": "<ISO-3166-1 alpha-2>", "type": "<onsite|hybrid|remote_region|remote_global|unclear>"}
  ```
  Leave `city` / `region` / `country` as `null` where unknown. `raw` is required.

